# Ashley Portfolio Website - Project Rules

## Technology Constraints
- **NO FRAMEWORKS**: Pure HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript only
- **NO DEPENDENCIES**: No external libraries, CDN links, or npm packages
- **STATIC SITE**: All files are static, no build process required

## File Naming Standards
- All asset files: lowercase with underscores (e.g., `ashley_zheng_band-aid_x_spiderman.png`)
- Thumbnails: Original filename + `_thumb` suffix
- Header image: Always named `header.png` in `assets/images/`

## Card Dimensions
- **Desktop**: 643px wide × 450px tall (wider than tall, ~3:2 ratio)
- **Layout**: 2 columns, 50px gap (equal horizontal and vertical spacing)
- **No Titles**: Cards display only thumbnail images, no text overlays

## Asset Organization
- `assets/images/` - Full-resolution images (including header)
- `assets/videos/` - Video files
- `assets/pdfs/` - PDF documents  
- `assets/thumbnails/` - Generated thumbnails (643×450px)

## Code Style
- Semantic HTML5 markup
- CSS: Component-based organization, responsive breakpoints at bottom
- JavaScript: Vanilla JS, class-based organization where appropriate
- Consistent indentation and formatting

## Responsive Breakpoints
- Desktop: Full 2-column layout
- Tablet: 1024px breakpoint (maintains 2 columns, adjusted heights)
- Mobile: 768px breakpoint (single column)
- Small Mobile: 480px breakpoint

## Memory Bank
- Always read memory bank files at start of tasks
- Update `activeContext.md` and `progress.md` after significant changes
- Document architectural decisions in `systemPatterns.md`
